post_text:
Today marks the start of National Hispanic Heritage Month, which aims to celebrate and honor the cultures, successes and many contributions of the Hispanic community. Through October 15, we will spotlight our THA Familia, resources and activities to celebrate this month and much more!
--
Hoy marca el inicio del Mes Nacional de la Herencia Hispana, que tiene como objetivo celebrar y honrar las culturas, los éxitos y muchas contribuciones de la comunidad hispana. ¡Hasta el 15 de octubre, destacaremos nuestra THA Familia, recursos y actividades para celebrar este mes y mucho más!
#tulsahonor #nerdyknights #HispanicHeritageMonth

This #FacilityFriday, the High School walls are starting to look more like THA with bulletin boards, college pennants and classroom posters! Progress continued in other parts of the building with the construction team using large saws to install fire doors in the basement.
--
¡Este #FacilityFriday, las paredes de la escuela preparatoria comienzan a parecerse más a THA con tableros de anuncios, banderines universitarios y carteles de aula! El progreso continuó en otras partes del edificio con el equipo de construcción usando sierras grandes para instalar puertas cortafuegos en el sótano.
#tulsahonor #nerdyknights

As we continue virtual learning, we have added numerous helpful resources to our website. These include both academic resources, like how to check out a book from Tulsa City-County Library, and family resources, such as citywide COVID-19 assistance opportunities for children and families. Visit www.tulsahonor.org and explore our "COVID-19" tab for more information.
--
A medida que continuamos con el aprendizaje virtual, hemos agregado numerosos recursos útiles a nuestro sitio web. Estos incluyen recursos académicos, cómo sacar un libro de la biblioteca de Tulsa City-County Library, y recursos familiares, como oportunidades de asistencia COVID-19 en toda la ciudad para niños y familias. Visite www.tulsahonor.org y explore nuestra pestaña "COVID-19" para obtener más información.
#tulsahonor #nerdyknights

The grant is being awarded to 5,000 families on a first-come, first-serve basis. Visit EKCO's website to learn more and apply today!

La subvención se otorga a 5,000 familias y se otorga por orden de llegada. Visite sitio web de EKCO para obtener más información y presentar su solicitud hoy.

Announcement! Our MS and HS Office Staff are working hard to answer your calls and return messages as fast as possible. We are receiving more calls than usual as scholars need help with technology. Please be sure to leave a message and we will call you back. You can also email mstechhelp@tulsahonor.org or hstechhelp@tulsahonor.org for technology support.
--
¡Anuncio! Nuestro personal de oficina de MS y HS está trabajando arduamente para responder sus llamadas y devolver mensajes lo más rápido posible. Estamos recibiendo más llamadas de lo habitual ya que los estudiantes necesitan ayuda con la tecnología. Asegúrese de dejar un mensaje y le devolveremos la llamada. También puede enviar un correo electrónico a mstechhelp@tulsahonor.org o hstechhelp@tulsahonor.org para obtener asistencia tecnológica.
#tulsahonor #nerdyknights

post_text:
It's #FacilityFriday! Although we are starting the year 100% virtually next week, our staff has been hard at work setting up the high school. This week, we unloaded 690 chairs and 690 desks from semi-trucks (with the AWESOME help of Gyorgy from
Church Transportation & Logistics, Inc). From unassembled in the truck to set up in the classroom, look at our strong staff members go!
--
¡Es #FacilityFriday! Aunque comenzaremos el año al 100% virtualmente la próxima semana, nuestro personal ha estado trabajando duro para establecer la escuela preparatoria. Esta semana, descargamos 690 sillas y 690 escritorios de camiones (con la INCREÍBLE ayuda de Gyorgy de Church Transportation & Logistics, Inc). Desde desmontados en el camión hasta montados en el aula, ¡mire a nuestros fuertes miembros del personal!
#tulsahonor #nerdyknights

We greatly appreciate our community partners, Grove Collaborative and National Alliance for Public Charter Schools, and their donation of cleaning and sanitization supplies. Your generosity will help us continue to keep our THA Familia safe.
--
Apreciamos enormemente a nuestros socios comunitarios, Grove Collaborative and National Alliance for Public Charter Schools, y su donación de suministros de limpieza y desinfección. Su generosidad nos ayudará a continuar manteniendo segura nuestra THA Familia.
#tulsahonor #nerdyknights
shared_text:
Grove Collaborative
July 28 at 2:00 PM ·

Grove Collaborative is proud to be partnering with the National Alliance for Public Charter Schools to donate $100,000 of healthy cleaning supplies to low-income school districts across the U.S.

Public schools have gone above and beyond to serve students and families throughout the pandemic. We’re honored to give back with a donation that’ll help the schools that decide to reopen, to do it safely.

From countless gallons of soap to thousands of containers of disinfectant wipes, reopening schools under the new healthy and safety guidelines will take a village. If you’d like to donate to a school in your community, we’ve created a Back to School Safely Bundle filled with natural, effective products to keep students and teachers well all year long.

Help your local school reopen safely with our complete collection of classroom cleaning essentials → grove.co/backtoschool

#tulsahonor #nerdyknights

shared_text:
LISC.ORG
In the Midst of Covid-19, 21 Charter Schools Receive "Spark" Grants | Local Initiatives Support Corporation

Local Initiatives Support Corporation (LISC)
May 12 at 11:56 AM ·

The LISC Charter School Financing Team has just selected 21 grantees to award $800,000 in the second round of the Spark Opportunity Grant Program. Congratulations to all of the grantees!

Spark Opportunity Grants range from $15,000 - $50,000. Charter schools can use the grants to plan, finance and build facilities that meet the needs of their communities. The Spark Opportunity Grant Program is made possible with financial support from the Walton Family Foundation. For more information about our second round grantees, visit our stories page. https://www.lisc.org/our-stories/story/spark-opportunity-grant-recipients-second-round.

#SparkOpportunityGrants #grants #predevelopment #charterschools #publicschools #facilities

Some families indicated that they were unable to pick up their work packet, Chromebook, or medication during the allotted hours. Additionally, some have reached out indicating that the Chromebook they check out might be faulty. To address these concerns, we are extending pick up for half a day on Monday.

From 12-5pm on Monday, March 30, families who have questions about a device that may not be working may bring it up to the school to swap out or troubleshoot. Additionally, families who have not yet checked out a Chromebook may come during this time. This will be the final Chromebook checkout time.

In order to ensure families have the support they need while also adhering with health-related guidelines, we are only checking out Chromebooks, packets, and medicine during this time. If you have additional questions, please call the MS office at (918) 833 – 9420 or the HS office at (918) 438 - 7204. Even though the offices will be closed, our front office staff will have calls directed to them, and they will be answering the phones during this time.

UPDATE: We passed out 231 chromebooks today. This means 231 Nerdy Knights will now have access to our online curriculum!

ÚLTIMAS NOTICIAS: Repartimos 231 computadora hoy. Esto quiere decir que 231 de nuestros Nerdy Knights ahora tendrán acceso a nuestro curriculum de internet!

💜 🤓 📚 🤓 💜

...

In the first 2 hours, we checked out over 50 Chromebooks! Remember, Chromebook checkout and packet pickup is 7:30am-4:30pm today and tomorrow. We encourage only 1 person per family to come pick up these resources.

¡En las primeras 2 horas, hemos prestado más de 50 Chromebooks! Recuerde, que el horario de los préstamos de Chromebooks y para recojer los paquetes de trabajo es de 7:30am-4:30pm, hoy y mañana. Pedimos que solo 1 persona por familia venga a recoger estos recursos.

post_text:
Given the direction of the CDC, Governor Stitt, and State Superintendent Hofmister and to slow the spread of COVID-19 in our community, THA will be closed through Friday April 3. At this time, students will return to classes no earlier than Monday, April 6. Please be advised that school closures may be longer.

Please, stay safe!

- - -

Debido la dirección del CDC, el gobernador Stitt, y la superintendente estatal Hofmeister y para frenar la propagación del coronavirus en nuestra comunidad, THA estará cerrado hasta el viernes 3 de abril. En este momento, los alumnos regresarán a clases no anted del lunes, 6 de abril. Tengan en cuenta que los cierres escolares pueden ser más largos.

Por favor, ¡manténganse sanos!

post_text: We are incredibly proud of our very own Nerdy Knight! Congratulations to Nathalia Mireles-Mota for winning first place in the Oklahoma Bar Association Law Day Contest for her essay about the Women’s Suffrage movement. post_text: As we celebrate #BlackHistoryMonth, we recognize our scholars have an amazing role model in Harriet Tubman who persevered and showed courage. Harriet Tubman risked her life to lead hundreds of enslaved African Americans to freedom as a conductor of the Underground Railroad. She taught the world that no matter what — you “keep going.” #tulsahonor #nerdyknights #blackhistorymonth

post_text:
Calling all 4th-9th grade families--Join the THA Familia! It's never too early to start thinking about college. Tulsa Honor Academy is a free college prep school with a mission for all scholars to go to and graduate from college. Our Middle School serves grades 5 through 8 and the High School will serve grades 9 and 10 in the 2020-2021 school year.

Tulsa Honor Academy is the only middle school in the Tulsa Metro area to receive an A on the state report card, and Friday is the final day to apply. Our scholars grow an average of 2 grade levels each year and we offer a variety of extracurricular activities.

Make sure to complete the application, list THA as your #1 choice and attach a photo ID and one proof of residency. If you have any questions, please call our front office at 918.833.9420. #choosetulsahonor #nerdyknights

post_text:
Tulsa Honor Academy is a local charter school with one mission: to equip all scholars with the academic skills, content knowledge and ethical character required for college graduation and life success. THA’s main focus is and always will be providing the very best for our scholars by offering an excellent academic education. In order to continue closing the opportunity gap, however, we must also offer a plethora of extra-curricular opportunities.

Thus, we are raising money on this #GivingTuesday to help fund extra-curricular opportunities for our scholars. With the assistance of donations collected, we will be able to help fund the THA Debate Team, THA Cooking Club, and THA Science Club. Every little bit helps. And on GivingTuesday Dec 3, Facebook will match a total of $7 million in donations first come, first served. Whether it's $5 or $500, every little bit helps!

Our Nerdy Knights appreciate your support!

post_text: Our College Readiness Advisor, Callie Kirk created a “Did you know” list on how a college degree can impact your future. Check out her list below! #nerdyknights #tulsahonor
shared_text:
Callie Kirk
September 6, 2019 at 4:57 PM ·

THA scholars learning about the ways a college degree can impact your life!

Did you know...

College graduates earn $1 to $4 million more over their lifetimes than high school graduates.

College graduates earn $17,500 more annually than high school graduates on average.

College graduates are 5x less likely to be imprisoned.

College graduates live 7 years longer than high school graduates on average.

College graduates report having good health 44% more than high school graduates.

College graduates volunteer at a rate 2.3x higher than high school graduates, contribute more than three times as much to charity, and vote and participate in politics at a significantly higher level.

If you can’t tell, I’m very excited for these future college graduates!

The high school building is almost complete, and we need your help! Join us on Saturday, July 27th from 8am-2pm. We'll be building furniture, setting up classrooms, and preparing the space for THA's Nerdy Knight 9th graders!

We'll provide a pizza lunch. If you have tools and work gloves, please bring them! We hope to see you here!

El edificio de la escuela preparatoria está casi terminado, ¡Y necesitamos su ayuda! Únase a nosotros el sábado, 27 de julio, de 8 am a 2 pm. ¡Construiremos muebles, arreglaremos salones de clase y prepararemos el espacio para los alumnos Nerdy Knight de 9º grado de THA!

Además, estaremos proporcionar un almuerzo de pizza. Si tiene herramientas y guantes de trabajo, favor de tráelos. ¡Esperamos verlo aquí!

post_text:
Finally... some good news!

Since the weather has finally collaborated with us, we WILL be able to host our 8th Grade Promotion Celebration Activities.

The Promotion Ceremony will be at Will Rogers High School. Scholars must report at 5:45 pm and the event starts at 6:15 pm.

The 8th Grade Lock-In will be at Tulsa Honor Academy and that will run from 9:00 pm to midnight. Parents can begin picking scholars up at 11:45 pm.

Time to celebrate!

- - -

Finalmente... ¡buenas noticias!

Ya que el clima está cooperando con nosotros, SI tendremos las Celebraciones de Promoción de 8vo grado.

¡Es tiempo de celebrar!

Thank you,
Ms. Clements

post_text:
Dear THA Familia,

We have had an alarmingly high number of students and adults sick over the last few weeks. Today we had so many staff members out sick that we could barely operate. Thus, we are canceling school for tomorrow. We are doing a deep cleaning of the building to hopefully get all of the germs out.

Please make sure that your son/daughter rests well, especially if they are sick. Hopefully, we will see you all on Thursday!

Sincerely,

Mrs. Elsie Urueta Pollock

---

Querida THA Familia,

Hemos tenido un número alarmantemente alto de estudiantes y adultos enfermos en las últimas semanas. Hoy tuvimos tantos miembros del personal enfermos que apenas pudimos mantener las operaciones escolares. Por lo tanto, estamos cancelando la escuela para mañana. Estamos haciendo una limpieza profunda del edificio para, con suerte, eliminar todos los gérmenes.

Por favor, asegúrese de que su hijo/a descanse bien, especialmente si están enfermos. Esperemos verlos a todos el jueves!

Sinceramente,

Sra. Elsie Urueta Pollock

post_text:
The Tulsa Public Schools Board of Directors voted last night to approve the Tulsa Honor Academy High School Expansion! We are thrilled for the opportunity to continue to work with the THA scholars and families in pursuit of our promise: that each and everyone of our scholars get to and graduates from college.

La Mesa Directiva de las Escuelas Públicas de Tulsa votaron anoche para aprobar la expansión de la Preparatoria de THA! Estamos emocionados por la oportunidad de poder continuar a servir los alumnos y las familias de THA para cumplir nuestra promesa: que cada uno de nuestros alumnos valla y se gradúe de la universidad.

#thadeservesahighschool #nerdyknights

T-minus 3 hours until the TPS School Board Meeting!!! We are asking for a show of support on social media sites.

Post a picture of you in your “THA Deserves a High School” shirt and tag Tulsa Honor Academy. To group all of the photos together, please use the hashtags #thadeservesahighschool, #nerdyknights and #tulsahonor.

post_text: On this #GivingTuesday, we aren't asking for monetary support. What our scholars need the most is the approval of the THA High School. Instead of giving THA money this year, we ask that you give your time. Please commit to coming to the TPS Board Meeting and show your support in person on December 3rd. Once again, we will need as much support as possible, so your presence is very much appreciated. We still have #THADeservesaHighSchool shirts available for $5.00. Please reach out if you would like to purchase one.
